  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Tondi-Gada Women Rice Production and Processing Project</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Sector: Rice Beneficiaries: 220 (98 women) Description: The grant will enable TGWMCA and its member farmers to produce 200ha of paddy (FARO 44 and FARO 46). The trainings and technical support to be provided through the grant will enable achievement of optimal yields from the farms. Paddy will be produced both under rain-fed and dry seasons conditions through irrigation. Paddy harvested will be packaged and bulked in the warehouse to be constructed under the proposed project. The bulked produce will be marketed to large scale commercial rice mills and other off-takers located in the project area. In addition, TGWMCA will establish two demonstration farms which will serve as farmer field schools where members will be trained on rice production good agronomic practices (GAP).</narrative>
  </description>
